  "prompt": "What is the amount of Maximum cash deposit in a saving bank account in a single financial year in India?",
  "response": "In India, there is no specific limit on the amount of cash that can be deposited into a savings bank account in a single financial year. However, if an individual deposits cash exceeding \u20b92 lakh (200,000 INR) in a single transaction or more than \u20b920 lakh (2 million INR) in a financial year, they must provide necessary income declarations, as this may trigger scrutiny from the tax authorities.\n\nIt's also important to be aware of KYC (Know Your Customer) norms and to report large cash deposits to avoid any issues with tax compliance. Always consult the latest guidelines from the Reserve Bank of India and other relevant authorities or a financial advisor for the most current information.",
